tting your letters of recommendation transferred to interfolio is an easy two step process 1 sign up with interfolio to establish an account 2 log into your cdc reference file service account and use the online mailing request form to request letters be mailed to interfolio we cannot accept requests via phone or in writing confirm your letters were sent to interfolio by checking the career development center's reference file service online if you don t see a record of your mailing request please contact the career development center's reference file service at 650 723 1548 login login to your account to submit a mailing request to have your letters of recommendation mailed to interfolio who needs a recommendation file letters of recommendation are necessary for graduate school applications fellowship applications teaching and other educational administration positions if you are an undergraduate who thinks there is even a small chance of attending graduate school soliciting recommendations is worthwhile for most other jobs letters of recommendation do not need to be solicited potential employers usually request only a list of names addresses and phone numbers rather than formal letters questions if you have any questions please feel free to email your questions to rfstudents mailman stanford edu or call 650 723 1548 back to top amcas faq amcas faq groups career development center printer friendly version calendar schedule an appointment graphic calendar pages schedule an appointment with a career counselor quick links calendar career fair schedule career planning handbook career library vault guided career path facebook linkedin what is the cdc copyright 2011 stanford university terms of use copyright complaints report a problem with this site
